main event: A UFO sighting was reported on 23 May 1949 at 1240 local time in Goose Bay, Labrador. The observation lasted 15-20 minutes and involved both radar and ground-visual confirmation.
interesting points: The observation lasted 15-20 minutes, allowing for a detailed study of the UFO.
The UFO was detected both on radar and visually from the ground, adding credibility to the sighting.
The UFO emitted a faint humming sound, indicating a potential propulsion system.
No photographs or sketches were included in the report, limiting visual evidence of the sighting.
The specific details like color, speed, altitude, and course of the UFO are blacked out, raising questions about the nature of the object.
witnesses: radar operators and ground visual observers
